  <prompt>
    <goal>Create docs/architecture/caching-architecture.md — document Redis caching strategy including distributed cache, request-scoped cache, token cache, embedding cache, and TTL tiers</goal>
    <context>The BFF API uses Redis as its primary caching layer (ADR-009) with multiple cache tiers: distributed cache for shared state, request-scoped cache for per-request deduplication, token cache for MSAL tokens, and embedding cache for AI vector embeddings. Each tier has distinct TTL policies. No architecture document captures this caching system end-to-end.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Use /docs-architecture skill structure
      - Source ALL content from actual code — do not invent cache strategies
      - Document each cache tier: distributed, request-scoped, token, embedding
      - Map TTL policies for each tier and key pattern
      - Include Redis configuration and connection management
      - Document cache invalidation strategies and eviction policies
      - Reference ADR-009 (Redis-first) constraint
      - Cite source files for every cache implementation
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
